      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "Hydrocarbon <b>A</b> has the formula C<sub>12</sub>H<sub>8</sub>. It absorbs 8 equivalents of H<sub>2</sub> on catalytic reduction over a palladium catalyst. On ozonolysis, only two products are formed: oxalic acid (HO<sub>2</sub>CCO<sub>2</sub>H) and succinic acid (HO<sub>2</sub>CCH<sub>2</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>CO<sub>2</sub>H). Write the reactions, and propose a structure for <b>A</b>.",
